#Tools and Technologies
The following software, hardware, and platforms were used to implement and evaluate the home-based Security Operations Center (SOC) for 
real-time threat detection, log analysis, and MITRE ATT&CK correlation using the ELK Stack:

#Software Stack:
1. ELK Stack:
• Elasticsearch: Used as the primary data storage and search engine for indexing and analyzing log data.
• Logstash: Configured for ingesting, parsing, and transforming logs from various endpoints.
• Kibana: Employed for data visualization, creating interactive dashboards, and monitoring security events in real-time.

2. Beats Agents:
• Filebeat: Deployed on Linux endpoints to collect and forward log data.
• Winlogbeat: Configured on Windows machines to collect and forward event logs.
• Auditbeat: Used for monitoring file integrity, user activity, and process execution on Linux systems.

3. Adversary Simulation Tools:
• Atomic Red Team: Utilized to simulate real-world attack techniques aligned with the MITRE ATT&CK framework.
• Metasploit: Used to perform penetration testing and emulate adversary tactics in a controlled environment.

#Virtualization Environment:
1. Oracle VirtualBox: Virtualization platform used for setting up virtual machines (VMs) in a controlled environment.
2. Guest Virtual Machines:
• Kali Linux: Configured as the attacker machine, running penetration testing tools and facilitating attack simulations using Metasploit and other frameworks.
• Ubuntu Server 24.04 LTS: Hosts the ELK Stack (Elasticsearch, Logstash,Kibana).
• Windows 10: Configured as the victim machine for testing simulated attacks.

#Hardware Specifications:
• Host Machine: Dell P144G201
• Processor: 11th Gen Intel Core i5-1135G7 @ 2.40GHz (4 cores)
• Memory: 16GB DDR4
• Storage: 250GB NVMe SSD

These tools and technologies were essential for setting up the project environment, collecting endpoint telemetry, simulating attacks, 
and analyzing the effectiveness of the SOC setup in detecting and responding to cybersecurity threats.
